<paragraph blockId="13.[112,647,723,908]" pageId="13" pageNumber="56">We only found two specimens of these small stems, partly decorticated but showing well-developed secondary xylem. There is no diagnostic feature allowing a specific identification. This genus extends up to the Early Permian where it has been found preserved as compressions at Autun (Igornay).</paragraph>
